dataset.title: Contour
dataset.description:
This feature layer contains all Linn County, Iowa 2 foot contours.

These contour lines were generated from a 2016 LiDAR project where LiDAR collection covering the City of Cedar Rapids was collected at approximately 3 foot spacing, and the rest of the County was collected at approximately 6 foot spacing.

The Elevation field within this feature layer represents the elevation above sea level in feet.

The Index Contour field within this feature layer represents whether the feature is a 10 foot index contour line.  Features within this layer have been filtered where this field equals 'Yes'.


Feature Layer Details
  • Update Frequency: Never
  • Feature Class Coordinate System: Web Mercator Auxiliary Sphere (wkid: 3857)

dataset.title: Sex Offender Cluster
dataset.description:
This feature layer contains Linn County registered sex offender clusters, i.e., more than one sex offender at a given location.  Linn County does NOT maintain this information.

See important notes below for methodology and source data.

Source Data:  State of Iowa Sex Offender Registry.  The following SQL clause is used to filter data: County = 'Linn'.  Please note, this will sometimes return data that is located outside Linn County boundaries.

Point location is derived from the Longitude and Latitude fields in the source data.  Points are NOT located based on an address.


Feature Layer Details
  • Update Frequency: Every weekday (Monday - Friday)
  • Feature Class Coordinate System: NAD 1983 (2011) Iowa North State Plane (wkid: 6463)
  • Max Visibility Scale: None

This item is a zip file that contains the contents listed below.  This allow users with ArcGIS for Desktop the ability to download current Linn County imagery through the selection of tiles.

For detailed instructions, please read the steps outlined in the ReadMe.pdf document.

Items included:
  1. ImageryDownload.mpk -- This is a map package that when unpackaged, contains a map document (.mxd) with 2 web service layers.  One is a reference layer used to orientate the user.  The second is a current image service layer by which the user can download selected tiles to their local machine or shared network drive.
  2. _ReadMe_.pdf -- This is a PDF document that outlines the steps necessary for a user to download imagery (raster) tiles to their local machine or shared network drive.  Please consult this documentation for a step-by-step workflow.

dataset.title: Sex Offender
dataset.description:
This feature layer contains Linn County registered sex offenders.  Linn County does NOT maintain this information.

See important notes below for methodology and source data.

Source Data:  State of Iowa Sex Offender Registry.  The following SQL clause is used to filter data: County = 'Linn'.  Please note, this will sometimes return data that is located outside Linn County boundaries.

Point location is derived from the Longitude and Latitude fields in the source data.  Points are NOT located based on an address.


Feature Layer Details
  • Update Frequency: Every weekday (Monday - Friday)
  • Feature Class Coordinate System: NAD 1983 (2011) Iowa North State Plane (wkid: 6463)
  • Max Visibility Scale: None
  • Min Visibility Scale: 1:288,895
  • Max Features Returned: 5,000
